{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859676921,"sessionID":"ses_28685e227ffe79cOB9S8Ppa9Kp","part":{"id":"prt_d797b25ea001HjV8Tcmzkt6anK","messageID":"msg_d797b0f37001bw1gOi5385fp4p","sessionID":"ses_28685e227ffe79cOB9S8Ppa9Kp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-010: Router 会话管理 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-010  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [session-routing/design.md](../../session-routing/design.md), [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md)\n\nThe Router Session Management component provides session lifecycle management, state tracking, and session affinity routing for the AgentCube HTTP reverse proxy. It integrates with the session store for persistence and uses the Kubernetes client-go library for sandbox metadata retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session Resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve sandbox sessions by session ID through the SessionManager interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Resolve existing session from store\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with session ID `sess-abc-123` exists in the session store\n- **WHEN** `SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession()` is called with the session ID\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the `SandboxInfo` with all session metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Session not found in store\n- **GIVEN** no sandbox exists with session ID `sess-missing-456`\n- **WHEN** `SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `store.ErrNotFound` error\n\n#### Scenario: Session lookup populates from Workload Manager on cache miss\n- **GIVEN** a session exists in Kubernetes but not in the local store\n- **AND** the Workload Manager API returns valid sandbox info for the session\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession()` is called with the session ID\n- **THEN** the system SHALL query the Workload Manager and return the sandbox info\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager unavailable during session lookup\n- **GIVEN** the session store does not contain the requested session\n- **AND** the Workload Manager API is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating the Workload Manager is unavailable\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session State Tracking\n\nThe system SHALL track and update session activity timestamps for lifecycle management.\n\n#### Scenario: Update last activity timestamp on request\n- **GIVEN** an active session with session ID `sess-active-789`\n- **WHEN** a request is routed through the proxy to that session\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with the current timestamp\n\n#### Scenario: Activity update failures are logged but non-blocking\n- **GIVEN** an active session and a failing store connection\n- **WHEN** the activity update fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log the error and continue processing the request\n\n#### Scenario: Session expiry is tracked\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a future timestamp\n- **WHEN** the session is stored via `StoreSandbox()`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL add the session to the expiry index with the expiration timestamp\n\n#### Scenario: Expired sessions are identifiable\n- **GIVEN** sessions with various expiration timestamps exist in the store\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes()` is called with `before=now`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return only sessions where `ExpiresAt <= now`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Affinity Routing\n\nThe system SHALL maintain session affinity by consistently routing requests to the same sandbox instance.\n\n#### Scenario: Route request to correct sandbox endpoint\n- **GIVEN** a session with entry points `[{Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.1.5:8080\", Path: \"/\"}]`\n- **WHEN** an invocation request is received for that session\n- **THEN** the reverse proxy SHALL forward the request to `10.0.1.5:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID header injection\n- **GIVEN** a valid session is resolved for an incoming request\n- **WHEN** the response is returned to the client\n- **THEN** the response SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session-id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Request with missing session ID\n- **GIVEN** a request without a valid session identifier\n- **WHEN** the router processes the request\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 400 with error message \"session ID required\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Lifecycle Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with the session lifecycle events from the Workload Manager.\n\n#### Scenario: Handle session creation notification\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox is created via the Workload Manager\n- **WHEN** the Session Manager receives the creation event\n- **THEN** the system SHALL store the session info via `StoreSandbox()`\n\n#### Scenario: Handle session deletion notification\n- **GIVEN** an existing session in the store\n- **WHEN** the Workload Manager sends a deletion notification\n- **THEN** the system SHALL remove the session via `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()`\n\n#### Scenario: Handle session update notification\n- **GIVEN** an existing session with outdated metadata\n- **WHEN** the Workload Manager sends an update with new entry points\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update the session via `UpdateSandbox()`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JWT Session Claims\n\nThe system SHALL generate JWT tokens with session-specific claims for authenticated routing.\n\n#### Scenario: Generate JWT with session ID claim\n- **GIVEN** a session ID `sess-jwt-001` and a `JWTManager` with valid RSA keys\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(map[string]interface{}{\"session_id\": \"sess-jwt-001\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a signed JWT containing claim `session_id: sess-jwt-001`\n\n#### Scenario: JWT includes standard claims\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with valid keys\n- **WHEN** a token is generated\n- **THEN** the token SHALL include `exp`, `iat`, and `iss: \"agentcube-router\"` claims\n\n#### Scenario: JWT expiration is enforced\n- **GIVEN** a JWT generated with 5-minute expiration\n- **WHEN** the token is validated after expiration\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with an expiration error\n\n#### Scenario: JWT signing with stored keys\n- **GIVEN** Kubernetes cluster is accessible\n- **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create or load the RSA key pair from Secret `picod-router-identity`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session Metadata Management\n\nThe system SHALL manage session metadata including kind, namespace, name, and status.\n\n#### Scenario: Store session with complete metadata\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxInfo` with Kind=\"AgentRuntime\", Namespace=\"default\", Name=\"runtime-1\", Status=\"Running\"\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL persist all metadata fields\n\n#### Scenario: Retrieve session metadata\n- **GIVEN** a stored session with complete metadata\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the `SandboxInfo` with all original metadata intact\n\n#### Scenario: List inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** sessions with varying last activity timestamps\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes()` is called with a threshold time\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return sessions where `lastActivity < threshold`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle session-related errors gracefully with appropriate error codes.\n\n#### Scenario: Session not found error\n- **GIVEN** a request for a non-existent session\n- **WHEN** the session lookup fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 404 with code `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND`\n\n#### Scenario: Store unavailable error\n- **GIVEN** the session store is unreachable\n- **WHEN** a session operation is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 503 with code `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid session ID format\n- **GIVEN** a request with malformed session ID containing invalid characters\n- **WHEN** the session ID is validated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 400 with code `VALIDATION_FAILED`\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\n### Modified Store Interface (from session-store/design.md)\n\nThe base store interface is extended to support session management operations:\n\n| Method | Change | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | **No change** | Used by router to track session activity |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | **No change** | Used for idle session detection |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | **No change** | Used for expired session cleanup |\n\n### SessionManager Interface (new)\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### SessionManager\n\n```go\n// SessionManager provides session resolution and lifecycle management.\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    // GetSandboxBySession resolves a sandbox by session ID.\n    // On cache miss, queries the Workload Manager API.\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// manager implements SessionManager.\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient     store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n```\n\n### JWTManager\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles RSA key generation and JWT token signing.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n\n// Methods:\n// - NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n// - GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n// - TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\n### Server struct (session-routing/design.md)\n\nThe `Server` struct includes session management:\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager    // NEW: Session management\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager       // NEW: JWT token management\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Session lookup | Direct store only | Store + Workload Manager fallback |\n| Session activity tracking | Not tracked | Updated on each request |\n| JWT generation | Not supported | RSA-signed JWT with session claims |\n| Session affinity | Basic routing | Header injection + consistent routing |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Session persistence |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | Shared types |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes Secret storage for keys |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Latest | HTTP/2 transport configuration |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager implementation |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager and token generation |\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | Server with session integration |\n| `pkg/router/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers with session resolution |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Route to AgentRuntime with session affinity |\n| GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Route to CodeInterpreter with session affinity |\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- The `SessionManager` interface replaces direct store access for session lookups\n- JWT tokens are now required for authenticated Workload Manager communication\n- Session activity tracking is enabled by default; no migration needed for existing sessions\n- RSA keys are automatically generated on first startup if not present in Kubernetes Secrets\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Sessions can be resolved from both store and Workload Manager fallback\n2. **Activity Tracking**: Last activity timestamp is updated on each routed request\n3. **Session Affinity**: Requests are consistently routed to the same sandbox endpoint\n4. **JWT Integration**: Tokens are generated with proper session claims and expiration\n5. **Error Handling**: Appropriate HTTP status codes and error messages for all failure scenarios\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775859676888,"end":1775859676906}}}}
