{"type":"text","timestamp":1775859701839,"sessionID":"ses_28685e227ffe79cOB9S8Ppa9Kp","part":{"id":"prt_d797c7d86001BnNlwU8Q7Z4gB2","messageID":"msg_d797c576c001L3QcI3fwLswEbm","sessionID":"ses_28685e227ffe79cOB9S8Ppa9Kp","type":"text","text":"I've successfully created the delta-spec.md file for AR-010 Router Session Management. The specification includes:\n\n## Summary of Contents\n\n### Requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios:\n1. **Session Resolution** (4 scenarios) - Resolving sessions from store and Workload Manager fallback\n2. **Session State Tracking** (4 scenarios) - Activity timestamps, expiry tracking\n3. **Session Affinity Routing** (3 scenarios) - Routing to correct endpoints, header injection\n4. **Session Lifecycle Integration** (3 scenarios) - Creation, deletion, update notifications\n5. **JWT Session Claims** (4 scenarios) - Token generation, claims, expiration, key storage\n6. **Session Metadata Management** (3 scenarios) - Complete metadata handling\n7. **Error Handling** (3 scenarios) - Error codes and HTTP status mappings\n\n### Additional Sections:\n- **Changes to Base Specification** - Modifications to existing interfaces\n- **New Interfaces** - SessionManager and JWTManager definitions\n- **Modified Interfaces** - Server struct extensions\n- **Behavioral Changes** - Before/after comparison table\n- **Dependencies** - Required packages\n- **File Index** - Expected implementation files\n- **API Endpoints Summary** - Router endpoints\n- **Migration Notes** - Migration guidance\n- **Acceptance Criteria Summary** - Key acceptance points\n\nThe document follows the OpenSpec format with 24 GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios covering all aspects of Router Session Management as defined in the base specifications.","time":{"start":1775859701835,"end":1775859701835}}}
